args:
Elisanne is the latest victimâ€”and while looking
for clues, the party discovers some peculiar
dolls with the souls of the dead sealed inside!
The group also makes a horrifying realization:
There is one more doll than there are bodies.
Do try to make your soul tasty for me, now!\nAaaaaah ha ha ha ha ha!
Elisanne, stop this now!\n...Amane, go! Run!
MUST you caterwaul so, Prince?\nAll of that shouting scared me!
Don't say it like you're surprised!\nSuch a tone may bring misfortune.
Sorry about that. Still, I'm relieved\nto see you well.
We were all watching out for each other,\nremember? There's no way Scylla could\nhave pulled any of her tricks last night.
DUDE, come ON! You can't just vanish\non the mysterious death island and then\npop back in whenever you feel like it!
I will ask again: How many are dead?
Luca, Cleo, and Ranzal. So three.
What is THAT supposed to mean?
If my estimation is correct,\nthere should be one more corpse.
Well, you're wrong! Everyone else is...is...
Rrrrrgh! DANGIT, Scylla! Get your scaly\nbutt out here so I can KICK IT ALREADY!
*sniff* I really hate this. It's stupid.\nWhy does everybody have to die?
What are you talking about, Mikoto?\nAnd how did you know Elisanne was dead?
It would be more expedient to show you.\nCome with me.
One of the caves dotting this island.\nIt seems they are all connected and\nshare a complex interior structure.
Take care, everyone.\nIt's darker here than you'd think.
Yeah, and not great footing, either.
Let us proceed cautiously. If we get lost,\nwe may not be able to find our way back.
It's so dark, I can't even see the face\nof the person standing next to me!
Heh. What if it's Scylla? WooOoOOOOoo!
Fear and wariness will only carry us so\nfar in this darkness, which means we've\nno choice but to trust each other.
Well, I'll be the bigger person and trust\nyou, Patiaâ€”so you should be grateful.
Well, seeing as I don't have a choice,\nI'll suppose I will trust you as well.
I'm more worried about getting lost in\nhere than I am about Scylla, actually.\nAre you sure this is okay, Mikoto?
Yes. Over the last few days, I've developed\na fair understanding of the cavern system.
But why were you in these caves\nto begin with?
The wind whispered to me of trapped\nsouls that forever wander this land.
It's just a bit farther now.
Dolls always up the ol' creepfactor. Brrr!
The reason I thought there were more\nvictims was because of these dolls.
I hope you are going to explain?
Yesterday, there were three dolls here.\nHowever, the number has increased\nsince last night.
Three victims as of yesterday...\nThen the number increases...
That's Ellyâ€”but it came from\none of the dolls!
Okay, I am NOT cool with ANY of this!
Mmm, yes. I thought it might be\nsomething like this...
Not something I know so much as\nsomething which caught my attention.\nNamely, Luca's body was too neat.

There were no external wounds on his
body. No signs of any abnormality.
It was as if his soul had simply been...
plucked out of his chest.
And if that's the case, maybe we can\nbring everyone back by returning their\nsouls to their bodies!
I know not. However, the waves I feel from\nthese dolls are unmistakably the pulsings\nof life, so the possibility may remain.
All right, so we free the souls that are\ntrapped in these dolls. But HOW?
Haaang on a second there, mystic bub.\nYou're saying each of these dolls is the\nsoul of one of our dead pals, right?
That means there's one too many!
Wait, she's right. Including Elly,\nwe've lost four of our friends...
